'''马里昂·戈登·“帕特”·罗伯逊'''（{{lang-en|'''Marion Gordon''' "'''Pat'''" '''Robertson'''}}，{{bd|1930年|3月22日|catIdx=R}}<ref name="officialbio">{{cite web |url=http://www.patrobertson.com/Biography/index.asp |title=Official biography |accessdate=2007-03-31 |archive-date=2021-01-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210125121734/http://www.patrobertson.com/Biography/index.asp |dead-url=no }}</ref>）是一位美国的传媒大亨，前[[美南浸信会|美南浸信会]]的牧师，支持[[基督教右派|保守派基督教]]的思想。目前担任瑞金大学校长，[[視博恩|視博恩]]（基督教广播网）主席。

罗伯逊是几个机构、公司和一所大学的创始人：包括[[視博恩|視博恩]]（CBN）、国际家庭娱乐公司（[[ABC家庭|ABC家庭频道]]）、[[瑞金大学|瑞金大学]]、美国法律与正义中心（ACLJ）、[[美国基督教联盟|美国基督教联盟]]、慈福行动国际救援与发展公司和CBN亚洲。<ref name="officialbio" /><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cc.org/about.cfm |title=About Us |publisher=Christian Coalition |accessdate=2007-03-31 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070308053058/http://www.cc.org/about.cfm |archivedate=2007-03-08 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>他也是一个畅销书作家，他的CBN基督教新闻和电视节目通过卫星在[[ABC家庭|ABC家庭频道]]直播，并通过CBN在各地的分支机构向全世界范围内播出。<ref name="officialbio" />

他的父亲是[[美国参议院|美国参议员]]蒂莫西·布莱恩·罗伯逊，罗伯逊是[[美南浸信会|美南浸信会信徒]]并积极与该教派多年的传道，但也持有[[靈恩派|靈恩派]]理论，并非传统的南浸信会信徒。<ref>{{cite journal|last=Sherrard|first=Brooke|journal=The Journal of Southern Religion|year=2007|url=http://jsr.fsu.edu/Volume11/Sherrard.htm|title=Review of: David John Marley, Pat Robertson: An American Life|accessdate=2014-11-17|archive-date=2021-02-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210224132959/http://jsr.fsu.edu/Volume11/Sherrard.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>他曾成为[[共和黨_(美國)|共和黨]]候选人参加[[1988年美国总统选举|1988年总统选举]]，但竞选失败。<ref>''New York Times'': [http://www.nytimes.com/1988/02/27/us/pat-robertson-a-candidate-of-contradictions.html?pagewanted=all&src=pm Pat Robertson: A Candidate of Contradictions.] {{Wayback|url=http://www.nytimes.com/1988/02/27/us/pat-robertson-a-candidate-of-contradictions.html?pagewanted=all&src=pm |date=20210308230137 }}  February 27, 1988.</ref><ref>OurCampaigns: [http://www.ourcampaigns.com/RaceDetail.html?RaceID=55211 1988 Republican Primary results.] {{Wayback|url=http://www.ourcampaigns.com/RaceDetail.html?RaceID=55211 |date=20210125024642 }}  February 01, 1988</ref>他成为美国[[保守主义|保守派]]基督教的一个公认的有影响力的且有争议的代表人物。<ref name="davidjohnmarley">David John Marley. Pat Robertson: An American Life. ISBN 978-0-7425-5295-1</ref>

==部分争议言论==
作为一个评论员，罗伯逊的节目偶尔会涉及有争议的话题，他经常会发表一些言论招致观众的批评或者支持。这些言论受到了国家和国际媒体的关注，也引起了政界人士的反应。

罗伯逊支持通过祈祷和仪式等信仰方式可以刺激神的同在的[[信心療法|信心療法]]。<ref>Randi, James (1989). The Faith Healers. Prometheus Books. ISBN 0-87975-535-0 pages 197–206.</ref>他告诫信徒，一些[[新教|新教]]教派可能本质是[[敌基督|敌基督]]<ref>"'I don't have to be nice to the spirit of the Antichrist: Right-wing TV evangelist and former Presidential candidate Pat Robertson is the man Bank of Scotland has chosen to spearhead its US subsidiary. Why?", by Greg Palast, Guardian Unlimited, May 23, 1999.</ref>，他祈祷[[熱帶氣旋|熱帶氣旋]]偏移<ref>''Daily Press'': [http://articles.dailypress.com/1995-08-18/news/9508180069_1_prayer-hurricane-felix-cbn Robertson Says Prayer Stalled Storm.] {{Wayback|url=http://articles.dailypress.com/1995-08-18/news/9508180069_1_prayer-hurricane-felix-cbn |date=20140322014311 }}  August 18, 1995.</ref>，谴责[[印度教|印度教]]如“[[邪靈|邪靈]]”<ref>Rajan, Valli J. (1995-07). "Christian Pat Robertson Denounces Hinduism as "Demonic"". Hinduism Today. http://www.hinduismtoday.com/modules/smartsection/item.php?itemid=3502 {{Wayback|url=http://www.hinduismtoday.com/modules/smartsection/item.php?itemid=3502 |date=20100117164329 }}.</ref>[[伊斯兰教|伊斯兰教]]如“[[撒旦|撒旦]]”。<ref>"Robertson says Islam isn't a faith of peace: Televangelist calls radicals 'demonic'", Sonja Barisic, March 14, 2006, Associated Press.</ref>罗伯逊谴责[[女权主义|女权主义]]的左翼观点<ref>"Equal Rights Initiative in Iowa Attacked", ''Washington Post'', August 23, 1992.</ref>，关于[[同性恋|同性恋]]的维权行动<ref>^ "California Governor Arnold Schwarzenegger Keeps Promise and Will Veto Abominable Homosexual 'Marriage' Bill Passed By Legislature Which Ignored Overwhelming Vote of California Voters in Proposition 22 Banning Homosexual 'Marriage'". Christian Coalition. 2005-09-09. {{cite web |url=http://www.cc.org/content.cfm?id=253 |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2007-03-31 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070203021848/http://www.cc.org/content.cfm?id=253 |archivedate=2007-02-03 }}. Retrieved 2007-03-31.</ref>，[[堕胎|堕胎]]<ref>"Abortion to Die by 1,000 Cuts After Today's Supreme Court Ruling". Christian Coalition. 2007-01-18. {{cite web |url=http://www.cc.org/archives/abortion/index.html |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2014-08-12 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071012214126/http://cc.org/archives/abortion/index.html |archivedate=2007-10-12 }}. Retrieved 2007-03-31.</ref>和自由主义的大学教授。<ref>"Right-Wing Watch", May 11, 2006, People for the American Way.</ref>

[[九一一袭击事件|九一一袭击事件]]当周，罗伯逊和[[傑瑞·法威爾|傑瑞·法威爾]]在节目上讨论袭击事件时法威爾说“[[美國公民自由聯盟|美國公民自由聯盟（ACLU）]]，[[异教|异教]]徒，堕胎者，以及女权主义者，男同性恋和[[女同性恋|女同性恋]]导致袭击事件的发生。”罗伯逊说，“我完全同意。”<ref>{{cite web |url=https://home.comcast.net/~joe.grabko/falwell.mp3 |title=Falwell speaks about WTC disaster, Christian Broadcasting Network |format=mp3 |accessdate=2012-03-11 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121019023622/https://home.comcast.net/~joe.grabko/falwell.mp3 |archivedate=2012-10-19 }}</ref>两人的言论被总统[[乔治·W·布什|乔治·W·布什]]严重批评<ref>David John Marley, ''Pat Robertson: an American life'' (2007) p 273</ref>，为此法威爾在之后发表了道歉声明。<ref>{{cite news |url=http://archives.cnn.com/2001/US/09/14/Falwell.apology/ |title=Falwell apologizes to gays, feminists, lesbians |publisher=CNN |date=2009-10-14 |accessdate=2010-09-07 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130401182609/http://archives.cnn.com/2001/US/09/14/Falwell.apology/ |archivedate=2013-04-01 }}</ref>

[[2005年颶風卡特里娜|颶風卡特里娜]]导致1836人遇难后不到两个星期，罗伯逊在9月12日播出的节目中暗示风暴是上帝对美国堕胎政策的惩罚。

2009年11月9日，罗伯逊说，伊斯兰教是“一个试图推翻世界各国政府一心想统治世界的暴力政治体系。”他继续阐述说：“你处理的不是宗教，而是一个政治制度，我认为我们应该像对待[[共产党|共产党]]员和[[法西斯|法西斯]]组织成员那样对待它的追随者。”<ref>{{cite news |last=Hamby |first=Peter |url=http://politicalticker.blogs.cnn.com/2009/11/18/mcdonnell-won%E2%80%99t-disavow-robertson%E2%80%99s-islam-remarks/ |title=McDonnell won’t disavow Robertson’s Islam remarks |publisher=CNN |date=2009-11-18 |accessdate=2010-09-07 |archive-date=2021-02-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210224031801/https://politicalticker.blogs.cnn.com/2009/11/18/mcdonnell-won%E2%80%99t-disavow-robertson%E2%80%99s-islam-remarks/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>

